Date: Fri, 2 Aug 2019 21:49:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] page flags: prioritize kasan bits over last-cpuid
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.2.10
Git-commit: ee38d94a0ad89890b770f6c876263cf9fcbfde84

[ Upstream commit ee38d94a0ad89890b770f6c876263cf9fcbfde84 ]

ARM64 randdconfig builds regularly run into a build error, especially
when NUMA_BALANCING and SPARSEMEM are enabled but not SPARSEMEM_VMEMMAP:

  #error "KASAN: not enough bits in page flags for tag"

The last-cpuid bits are already contitional on the available space, so
the result of the calculation is a bit random on whether they were
already left out or not.

Adding the kasan tag bits before last-cpuid makes it much more likely to
end up with a successful build here, and should be reliable for
randconfig at least, as long as that does not randomize NR_CPUS or
NODES_SHIFT but uses the defaults.

In order for the modified check to not trigger in the x86 vdso32 code
where all constants are wrong (building with -m32), enclose all the
definitions with an #ifdef.

